-A.Description: If present, list the requested object(s) across all namespaces. Namespace in current context is ignored even if specified with --namespace.

--all-namespaces=false.Description: If present, list the requested object(s) across all namespaces. Namespace in current context is ignored even if specified with --namespace.

--allow-missing-template-keys=true.Description: If true, ignore any errors in templates when a field or map key is missing in the template. Only applies to golang and jsonpath output formats.

--chunk-size=500.Description: Return large lists in chunks rather than all at once. Pass 0 to disable. This flag is beta and may change in the future.

--field-selector=''.Description: Selector (field query) to filter on, supports '=', '==', and '!='.(e.g. --field-selector key1=value1,key2=value2). The server only supports a limited number of field queries per type.

-f.Description: Filename, directory, or URL to files identifying the resource to get from a server.

--filename=[].Description: Filename, directory, or URL to files identifying the resource to get from a server.

--ignore-not-found=false.Description: If the requested object does not exist the command will return exit code 0.

-k.Description: Process the kustomization directory. This flag can't be used together with -f or -R.

--kustomize=''.Description: Process the kustomization directory. This flag can't be used together with -f or -R.

-L.Description: Accepts a comma separated list of labels that are going to be presented as columns. Names are case-sensitive. You can also use multiple flag options like -L label1 -L label2...

--label-columns=[].Description: Accepts a comma separated list of labels that are going to be presented as columns. Names are case-sensitive. You can also use multiple flag options like -L label1 -L label2...

--no-headers=false.Description: When using the default or custom-column output format, don't print headers (default print headers).

-o.Description: Output format. One of json|yaml|name|go-template|go-template-file|template|templatefile|jsonpath|jsonpath-as-json|jsonpath-file|custom-columns-file|custom-columns|wide See custom columns [http:s//kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/overview/#custom-columns], golang template [http://golang.org/pkg/text/template/#pkg-overview] and jsonpath template [http:s//kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/jsonpath/].

--output=''.Description: Output format. One of json|yaml|name|go-template|go-template-file|template|templatefile|jsonpath|jsonpath-as-json|jsonpath-file|custom-columns-file|custom-columns|wide See custom columns [http:s//kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/overview/#custom-columns], golang template [http://golang.org/pkg/text/template/#pkg-overview] and jsonpath template [http:s//kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/jsonpath/].

--output-watch-events=false.Description: Output watch event objects when --watch or --watch-only is used. Existing objects are output as initial ADDED events.

--raw=''.Description: Raw URI to request from the server.  Uses the transport specified by the kubeconfig file.

-R.Description: Process the directory used in -f, --filename recursively. Useful when you want to manage related manifests organized within the same directory.

--recursive=false.Description: Process the directory used in -f, --filename recursively. Useful when you want to manage related manifests organized within the same directory.

-l.Description: Selector (label query) to filter on, supports '=', '==', and '!='.(e.g. -l key1=value1,key2=value2)

--selector=''.Description: Selector (label query) to filter on, supports '=', '==', and '!='.(e.g. -l key1=value1,key2=value2)

--server-print=true.Description: If true, have the server return the appropriate table output. Supports extension APIs and CRDs.

--show-kind=false.Description: If present, list the resource type for the requested object(s).

--show-labels=false.Description: When printing, show all labels as the last column (default hide labels column)

--show-managed-fields=false.Description: If true, keep the managedFields when printing objects in JSON or YAML format.

--sort-by=''.Description: If non-empty, sort list types using this field specification.  The field specification is expressed as a JSONPath expression (e.g. '{.metadata.name}'). The field in the API resource specified by this JSONPath expression must be an integer or a string.

--template=''.Description: Template string or path to template file to use when -o=go-template, -o=go-template-file. The template format is golang templates [http://golang.org/pkg/text/template/#pkg-overview].

-w.Description: After listing/getting the requested object, watch for changes.

--watch=false.Description: After listing/getting the requested object, watch for changes.

--watch-only=false.Description: Watch for changes to the requested object(s), without listing/getting first.
